e visiting a city thats not your own youre going to need some tips for where to go what to do etc yes you could yelp it  but wouldnt you rather hear it straight from a local you trust” – mashable aiming to be more than a guidebook this website and app focuses on local experiences in destinations recommended by people living in those cities – forbes “best travel apps for ” maybe you’d rather steer clear of the welltrodden sights and slip into the local scene localeur solicits advice from you guessed it locals” – time “the  best free apps for travel junkies” by amassing a community of local tastemakers – artists entrepreneurs and creators who are constantly seeking the best of their cities – localeurs taking big steps to make our app better than ever dining out in nyc hunting for live music in austin shopping in chicago with recommendations from over  major us cities and small towns too localeurs got you covered whether youre spending a weekend in a big city or heading out on an epic road trip our community can help you find authentically local destinations wherever you roam plus you can now save your favorites and share them with friends without having to log in via facebooklocaleur helps you• discover thousands of places to experience local in us cities• learn localsonly tips on the best places to eat get a drink shop and get outdoors• find nearby places by category• save your favorites and build your itinerary for an upcoming trip featuring nearly  and counting of the country’s best restaurants bars shops and places localeur gives you a much more authentic credible array of recommendations than anything you’ll find on cluttered anonymous review sites here’s some more love we’ve gottenthe today show called us a “musthave travel app” msn and mtv both named us one of the best apps for traveling to a new city black enterprise named us one of “ apps to help you travel like a local” men’s journal called localeur one of  apps no traveler should leave home without huffingt